# How to get a Clerk JWT for testing this API
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option A — browser (fastest)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Visit https://YOUR-APP.clerk.accounts.dev (your Clerk frontend URL)
# 2. Sign up / sign in.
# 3. Open DevTools console:
#       await Clerk.session.getToken()                          // 60s lifetime
#       await Clerk.session.getToken({ template: 'dev' })       // long-lived
#    (Create the 'dev' template once in Clerk Dashboard → JWT Templates,
#     set lifetime to e.g. 86400 seconds.)
# 4. Copy the JWT into .env as TOKEN=...
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option B — fully headless via Clerk Backend API
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Requires:
#   - CLERK_SECRET_KEY in .env (sk_test_...) — Clerk Dashboard → API Keys
#   - A user_id (Clerk Dashboard → Users → click user → copy ID, e.g. user_2abc...)
#
# Replace USER_ID below with the actual id, then send each request in order.

@clerkApi = https://api.clerk.com/v1
@userId = user_REPLACE_ME

### 1. Create a session for that user
# @name createSession
POST {{clerkApi}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv CLERK_SECRET_KEY}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{userId}}"
}

### 2. Mint a JWT for that session, then paste the `jwt` field into .env as TOKEN
POST {{clerkApi}}/sessions/{{createSession.response.body.id}}/tokens
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv CLERK_SECRET_KEY}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 2b. Mint a JWT using the long-lived 'dev' template
POST {{clerkApi}}/sessions/{{createSession.response.body.id}}/tokens/dev
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv CLERK_SECRET_KEY}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Verify your token works against the Kora API
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pick any authenticated endpoint. If the token is invalid you get 401.
# The first authenticated request also creates your User row (JIT provisioning).

### whoami — verify token + see your User row (JIT-provisioned on first hit)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/whoami
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv TOKEN}}

### My clubs — clubs I'm Admin or staff of (empty for plain Players)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me/clubs
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv TOKEN}}
